RUMSFELD V. FAIR, A FREE SPEECH SETBACK OR STRATEGIC MILITARY VICTORY?
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EDDAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EDDAE_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
I. Introduction
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0ENDAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0ENDAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The so-called \u8220\'3fDon\rquote t Ask/Don\rquote t Tell/Don\rquote t Pursue\u8221\'3f policy in the U.S. armed forces, as it pertains to homosexuals, has been controversial ever since its adoption in the 1990s
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F1333572300_ID0E3DAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F1333572300_ID0E3DAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F1333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
1
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 and continues to roil public and legal debate. The Department of Defense\rquote s (hereinafter \u8220\'3fDOD\u8221\'3f) current policy prohibits openly gay individuals\u8212\'3fthose who publicly profess their homosexuality\u8212\'3ffrom enlisting or serving in the armed forces.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F2333572300_ID0EEEAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F2333572300_ID0EEEAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F2333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
2
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In contrast, nearly all law schools have adopted nondiscrimination policies that prohibit campus recruiting by employers who do not endorse or abide by the school\rquote s nondiscrimination policies.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F3333572300_ID0EJEAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F3333572300_ID0EJEAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F3333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
3
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 These nondiscrimination policies protect, inter alia, discrimination against any individual on the basis of sexual orientation.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F4333572300_ID0EOEAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F4333572300_ID0EOEAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F4333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
4
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EVEAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EVEAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
When Congress enacted the Solomon Amendment,
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F5333572300_ID0E2EAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F5333572300_ID0E2EAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F5333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
5
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 it threatened to cut off federal funding to those universities and educational institutions that 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_100319_76_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_100319_76_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*76
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 did not allow the military to recruit on substantially the same basis as other recruiters.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F6333572300_ID0EFFAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F6333572300_ID0EFFAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F6333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
6
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Universities and law schools, already in disagreement with the DOD\rquote s policy towards homosexuals in the military, seized upon the opportunity to fight the policy\u8212\'3falbeit indirectly\u8212\'3fin federal court.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F7333572300_ID0EKFAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F7333572300_ID0EKFAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F7333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
7
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0ERFAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0ERFAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The resulting showdown culminated in litigation before the United States Supreme Court, pitting law schools and law professors from some of the nation\rquote s most prestigious institutions
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F8333572300_ID0EXFAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F8333572300_ID0EXFAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F8333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
8
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 against the Federal Government. The ultimate issue involved the breadth of Congress\rquote  power to withdraw millions of dollars from these institutions, as well as its obligation to \u8220\'3fraise and support Armies\u8221\'3f and \u8220\'3fmaintain a Navy\u8221\'3f as required in Article I of the U.S. Constitution.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F9333572300_ID0EGGAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F9333572300_ID0EGGAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F9333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
9
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0ENGAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0ENGAE_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
II. Procedural Background
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EXGAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EXGAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On March 6, 2006, the United States Supreme Court decided the case of Rumsfeld v. Forum for Academic and Institutional Rights
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F10333572300_ID0E4GAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F10333572300_ID0E4GAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F10333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
10
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (FAIR). The Solomon Amendment was drafted by Congress in order to grant conditional federal funding to institutions of higher education that give the military the same access to on-campus recruiting projects as other employers.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F11333572300_ID0EFHAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F11333572300_ID0EFHAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F11333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
11
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 FAIR, however, objected to allowing military recruiters on university and law school campuses because of DOD prohibitions of openly gay participation in the armed forces.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F12333572300_ID0ELHAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F12333572300_ID0ELHAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F12333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
12
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 FAIR member law schools had adopted policies opposing discrimination based on, among other factors, sexual orientation.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F13333572300_ID0EPHAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F13333572300_ID0EPHAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F13333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
13
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EWHAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EWHAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In 2003, FAIR sought a preliminary injunction against enforcement of the Solomon Amendment,
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F14333572300_ID0E3HAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F14333572300_ID0E3HAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F14333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
14
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 which allowed the DOD to deny specified 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_100319_77_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_100319_77_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*77
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 federal funds to any institution of higher education \u8220\'3fthat either prohibits, or in effect prevents\u8221\'3f military recruiters \u8220\'3ffrom gaining entry to campuses.\u8221\'3f
}
