103
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In this case, the Court rejected the law schools\rquote  claim that the Solomon Amendment compelled them to subsidize the government\rquote s speech by putting demands on the law schools\rquote  employees and resources.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F104333572300_ID0EAHAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F104333572300_ID0EAHAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F104333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
104
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Rather, the Court found that, although recruiting assistance provided by law schools frequently includes some elements of speech via email and posting notices, it does not require any type of expression as 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_100319_87_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_100319_87_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*87
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 noted in previous case law.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F105333572300_ID0ELHAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F105333572300_ID0ELHAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F105333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
