{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EIIAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EIIAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
A second argument advanced by law schools claiming that the Solomon Amendment violated their First Amendment right to free speech was rooted in the view that, because schools were required to permit military recruiters on campus, they were forced to accommodate the military\rquote s speech.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
