{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EETAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EETAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The Court\rquote s unanimous decision marked a clear victory for the military\rquote s interest in recruiting at schools receiving federal funds. The challenge by a coalition of 36 law schools and faculties was decisively rebuffed as an argument without merit. The 8-0 decision made it abundantly clear that Congress may condition federal funding upon the schools\rquote  granting equal recruitment access to the military. The rationale behind the unanimous decision, a type of outcome that is rare in major First Amendment cases, is discussed in more detail below.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EZTAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EZTAG_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
A. Analysis of the Court\rquote s Considerable Deference Given to Congress\rquote  Power to Raise and Support the Military
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EDUAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EDUAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The power of Congress to provide for the common defense is unquestionably \u8220\'3fbroad and sweeping.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F145333572300_ID0ELUAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F145333572300_ID0ELUAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F145333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
145
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 As such, the Court affords a large amount of leeway to any such law that exercises that authority as long as the law does not exceed its constitutional limits.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F146333572300_ID0EQUAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F146333572300_ID0EQUAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F146333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
146
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Historically, the roots of such deference to Congress\rquote  use of its military-raising power are well- 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_100319_91_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_100319_91_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*91
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 recognized. In early American history, George Washington faced huge obstacles in securing adequate resources and men to wage an effective war against the British.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F147333572300_ID0E4UAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F147333572300_ID0E4UAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F147333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
147
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Under the Articles of Confederation, Congress\rquote  only avenue for securing soldiers was to requisition them from each state based on the states\rquote  quota of service-eligible men.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F148333572300_ID0ECVAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F148333572300_ID0ECVAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F148333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
148
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Since each state was responsible for equipping its troops and appointing officers, Congress had to find a way to fund them.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F149333572300_ID0EHVAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F149333572300_ID0EHVAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F149333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
149
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The system basically broke down to rely almost exclusively on the wealth of each state.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F150333572300_ID0EMVAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F150333572300_ID0EMVAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F150333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
150
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 This requisition system failed to raise the needed men to fight, coming \u8220\'3fperilously close to handing victory to the British in the Revolutionary War.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F151333572300_ID0E1VAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F151333572300_ID0E1VAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F151333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
151
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 States often held back resources.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F152333572300_ID0E6VAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F152333572300_ID0E6VAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F152333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
152
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Challenged with this scenario, Congress reformed the system, empowering within the Constitution the Federal Government\rquote s ability to raise its own military without state meddling, using taxes and duties on individuals to pay for the effort.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F153333572300_ID0EDWAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F153333572300_ID0EDWAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F153333572300_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
153
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EKWAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EKWAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
By analyzing modern-day recruitment trends and the political climate we live in, the importance of recruiting talented military lawyers is obvious. The Court pointed out that military recruiting is not only a substantial government interest, but that it would be achieved far less effectively if the military were to recruit only on less advantageous terms as other employers.
