{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
There is no doubt that law professors and universities have and will continue to seek the abolition of the military\rquote s \u8220\'3fDon\rquote t Ask\u8221\'3f policy. In this case, they spotlighted their own profession and beliefs by putting themselves in the limelight of the biggest legal stage in the country. Self-aggrandizement aside, law professors could have better focused their arguments in support of gay rights by urging the abolition of the current military policy as a way of fully integrating the armed forces, rather than framing the issue as a violation of their own perceived oppression under the Solomon Amendment. However, even under an alternate theory of \u8220\'3fsocial integration,\u8221\'3f the law professors would not have been able to escape the realization that the American military is undoubtedly one of the most integrated institutions in the nation, even exceeding that of the so-called elite law schools and professors who brought this case.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EHDBG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EHDBG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Nevertheless, even had the professors attacked the military\rquote s homosexual policies directly, the armed forces\rquote  lead in social integration is another reason why the Supreme Court may have given a great measure of deference to its judgments in the realm of national defense and maintenance of unit cohesion and morale. No doubt, the same elite law professors who fought to limit their own students\rquote  access to views conflicting with their own would also ordain themselves better-suited to transform the military\rquote s culture from the heights of their ivory towers.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EWDBG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EWDBG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
If nothing else, this case will stand as a reminder that the law\u8212\'3fat least as it is practiced by the United States Supreme Court\u8212\'3fwill not be influenced by elitist political concerns under Chief Justice Roberts\rquote  watch. It would serve FAIR and its supporters well to re-familiarize themselves with the basics of First Amendment jurisprudence and more fully cultivate and teach the art of legal reasoning before they bring another unsupportable case.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
